Interface RangedProduct<S,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - type carried by the first operand to the product
    T - type carried by the second operant to the product, may be identical to the first
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RangedProductList

    public interface RangedProduct<S,T>
    Factory class used to create new product instances and define common methods for products.
    Author:
    Patrick Finnerty

      • rangeCheck

        default void rangeCheck(long outer,
                        long inner)
        Checks if the provided long index point is included in the range this instance is defined on, i.e. if method get(long, long) can be safely called with the provided parameter.
        Parameters:
        outer - the long value whose represents the outer index of the point
        inner - the long value whose represents the inner index of the point
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the provided index is outside the range this instance is defined on

      • subView

        RangedProduct<S,T> subView(SquareRange range)
        Provides a SquareRangedList of the elements contained in this instance on the specified SquareRange.

        If the provided range exceeds the indices contained in this instance the method will return the elements it contains that fit within the provided range.

        Parameters:
        range - range of indices of which a copy is desired
        Returns:
        a ranged list of the elements contained in this SquareRangedList that fit in the provided range.
